  "texts": [
    "Content freedom is defined as the scope and variety of potential content that can fill the placeholder.",
    "For instance, the placeholder for the \"content\" section in tweets allows for a broad spectrum of topics and styles, thereby granting it high content freedom.",
    "Conversely, the placeholder for \"event_name\" in a calendar event retrieval response is more restricted, thus having lower content freedom.",
    "Based on this criterion, we instructed GPT-4 to classify user cases into two groups based on their levels of content freedom.",
    "Given that the outputs can vary, we generated responses three times and used majority voting to determine the final category for each user case."
  ],
